<emphasis id="EAAFF9294336C918FE11046CD37FB93F" box="[389,578,272,298]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ph. sigma sigma</emphasis>
(P. 
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA4336C918FDFD046CD3C3B93F" author="Rossi P" box="[617,766,271,298]" journalOrPublisher="Typis Thomae Masi &amp; Sociorum, Liburni" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" refId="ref3794" refString="Rossi P (1790) Fauna Etrusca sistens insecta quae in provinciis Florentina et Pisana praesertim collegit, Tomus primus. Typis Thomae Masi &amp; Sociorum, Liburni." title="Fauna Etrusca sistens insecta quae in provinciis Florentina et Pisana praesertim collegit, Tomus primus" type="book" year="1790">Rossi, 1790</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
], and also from 
<taxonomicName id="1FDB5EB84336C918FC45046CD019B958" authority="Sciaky, 1991" authorityName="Sciaky" authorityYear="1991" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dacicus">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294336C918FC45046CD569B93F" box="[977,1108,272,298]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ph. dacicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA4336C918FF18044FD019B958" author="Sciaky R" box="[140,292,307,333]" journalOrPublisher="Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="53 - 78" part="1990" refId="ref3823" refString="Sciaky R (1991) Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa. Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69 [1990]: 53 - 78." title="Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa" type="journal article" year="1991">Sciaky, 1991</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="A0CC65AB4336C918FEA2044FD09BB958" box="[310,422,307,333]" name="Romania" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Romania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="A0CC65AB4336C918FE21044FD32AB95B" box="[437,535,307,334]" name="Ukraine" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
) by its characteristic colouration (see figures in 
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA4336C918FF18042AD01BB964" author="Sciaky R" box="[140,294,342,369]" journalOrPublisher="Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="53 - 78" part="1990" refId="ref3823" refString="Sciaky R (1991) Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa. Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69 [1990]: 53 - 78." title="Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa" type="journal article" year="1991">Sciaky, 1991</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA4336C918FEFD042BD33FB964" author="Wrase DW" box="[361,514,342,369]" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitrage" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="807 - 813" part="37" refId="ref3956" refString="Wrase DW (2005) Description of a new Philorhizus species from Greece and faunistic notes on other species previously described (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Lebiini). Linzer biologische Beitrage 37 (1): 807 - 813." title="Description of a new Philorhizus species from Greece and faunistic notes on other species previously described (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Lebiini)" type="journal article" year="2005">Wrase, 2005</bibRefCitation>
), the almost rectilinearly narrowed long tempora, the characteristic form of the pronotum with its obtuse posterior angles angled strongly forward (at about the length of antennomere 2), and therefore its base laterally strongly rounded toward the posterior angles, and by the different construction of its median lobe and the striking structure of its internal sac (compare figures in 
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA4336C918FE93077AD099BA34" author="Sciaky R" box="[263,420,518,545]" journalOrPublisher="Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="53 - 78" part="1990" refId="ref3823" refString="Sciaky R (1991) Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa. Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana 69 [1990]: 53 - 78." title="Revisione dei Philorhizus della regione paleartica con descrizione di quattro nuovi taxa" type="journal article" year="1991">Sciaky, 1991</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA4336C918FE7E077BD3BBBA34" author="Wrase DW" box="[490,646,518,545]" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitrage" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="807 - 813" part="37" refId="ref3956" refString="Wrase DW (2005) Description of a new Philorhizus species from Greece and faunistic notes on other species previously described (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Lebiini). Linzer biologische Beitrage 37 (1): 807 - 813." title="Description of a new Philorhizus species from Greece and faunistic notes on other species previously described (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Lebiini)" type="journal article" year="2005">Wrase, 2005</bibRefCitation>
). For better distinction we present an identification key (see below).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="90C176B04336C918FF2D0731D062BAC5" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D864253B4336C918FF2D0731D062BAC5" blockId="5.[140,1108,166,1038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294336C918FF2D0731D006BA72" bold="true" box="[185,315,589,615]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Etymology</emphasis>
It gives us great pleasure to be able to dedicate this new species to our colleague and friend Dr. Werner A. Marggi (Thun), well-known specialist in 
<taxonomicName id="1FDB5EB84336C918FC6A070CD188BAB8" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carabidae</taxonomicName>
, who collected (together with Dr. Charles Huber, 
<collectingRegion id="1A1FEBD94336C918FD7B07E8D21ABABB" box="[751,807,660,686]" country="Switzerland" name="Bern" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Bern</collectingRegion>
) the first known specimen of the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="90C176B04336C918FF2D07A5D322BB02" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D864253B4336C918FF2D07A5D322BB02" blockId="5.[140,1108,166,1038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294336C918FF2D07A5D06DBAE6" bold="true" box="[185,336,729,755]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Distribution</emphasis>
Up to now only known from the 
<typeStatus id="07609B994336C918FD5807A6D3C1BAE1" box="[716,764,730,756]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">type</typeStatus>
locality in the Taygetos Massif and most likely an endemic species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="90C176B04336C918FF2D065CD57ABC1B" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="D864253B4336C918FF2D065CD57ABC1B" blockId="5.[140,1108,166,1038]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="EAAFF9294336C918FF2D065CD025BB2F" bold="true" box="[185,280,800,826]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Habitat</emphasis>
The specimens from 2007 were collected from low down on stones in subalpine meadows at altitudes of 
<quantity id="1F2388DE4336C918FD80063FD3F3BB4B" box="[532,718,835,862]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="m" value="2200.0" valueMax="2400.0" valueMin="2000.0">
<date id="AC6503FB4336C918FD80063FD38CBB48" box="[532,689,835,862]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="2000" valueMax="2400">2000 to 2400</date>
m
</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="40E039BE4336C918FD49063FD21CBB48" box="[733,801,835,861]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[140,174,1090,1112]" captionTargetBox="[140,1108,430,1070]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[137,1111,165,1070]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitat of Philorhizus marggii n. sp." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2652729/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). The stones were well embedded in the ground and surrounded by grass, which was taller than in the meadow grazed by goats and sheep. Beetles’ activity on the plants is therefore likely to be typical for many other lebiine carabids (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="BC4A58CA4336C918FD1906D1D228BBD2" author="Stork NE" box="[653,789,941,967]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="173 - 306" part="68" refId="ref3926" refString="Stork NE (1980) A scanning electron microscope study of tarsal adhesive setae in the Coleoptera. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 68: 173 - 306." title="A scanning electron microscope study of tarsal adhesive setae in the Coleoptera" type="journal article" year="1980">Stork 1980</bibRefCitation>
). The specimen from 1997 was collected in the montane zone close to a small pond. These records indicate that the species probably occurs in the middle and higher altitudes of Mount Taygetos.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
